1
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:57,240
One year,

2
00:01:57,960 --> 00:01:59,880
I had the hallway renovated.

3
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,640
I hired a relative to take the job.

4
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:08,000
Turns out there were quality issues.

5
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:11,840
One resident slipped
on the stairs at night and died.

6
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:14,080
I figured

7
00:02:14,160 --> 00:02:17,280
I should fix it before it got worse,
so I redid the hallway.

8
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:19,000
But I had no money left.

9
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:21,160
So I secretly

10
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:25,440
took materials from maintenance
and got some supplies.

11
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:26,920
I set up a small shack

12
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,600
in the parking garage
and stashed the materials there.

13
00:02:32,440 --> 00:02:33,280
Officer Ran,

14
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:37,440
why did you go to the garage?

15
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:40,920
I just thought, once I had enough,

16
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,000
I'd fix it properly.

17
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:46,120
You tell me, why'd he get so much cement?

18
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:49,640
This cement must be about 100 kilos.

19
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,120
But then,

20
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:55,480
that year,

21
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:57,960
Ju… July…

22
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:15,440
Rats. I love catching rats.

23
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:17,480
Xiaohe, slow down.

24
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:19,400
Xiaohe.

25
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:23,680
Uncle Ran, this underground maze
is so cool!

26
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:24,800
Xiaohe,

27
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:28,320
stay close to me.

28
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:30,000
What if a rat suddenly jumps out?

29
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:52,440
<i>How would I know</i>

30
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:57,280
<i>there was a head and two arms</i>
<i>in that tool bag?</i>

31
00:03:59,720 --> 00:04:01,920
I did think about calling the police.

32
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:02,960
Did you?

33
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:29,200
- Who is it?
- <i>Qian Dajun.</i>

34
00:04:29,280 --> 00:04:30,800
<i>You brat!</i>

35
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:33,440
Dad.

36
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:35,000
<i>Who are you calling Dad?</i>

37
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:37,480
<i>When are you going to sell</i>
<i>the place in Yuanlongli?</i>

38
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,000
Soon.

39
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:41,400
- Soon.
- <i>Not a chance.</i>

40
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:42,840
<i>I've heard about it!</i>

41
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,360
<i>They say that place eats people.</i>

42
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:46,480
<i>No one dares live there.</i>
<i>Prices are dropping like crazy.</i>

43
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:47,520
<i>Back then,</i>

44
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:50,240
<i>rumors were going around</i>
<i>that the place was killing people.</i>

45
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:52,400
<i>If I'd called the police,</i>

46
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:56,720
<i>neither my place nor my relatives'</i>
<i>would've sold.</i>

47
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:59,200
<i>After thinking it through,</i>

48
00:04:59,280 --> 00:05:02,440
<i>I decided to keep it quiet.</i>

49
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:08,360
I figured I'd find a safer place,

50
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:10,560
hide it first,

51
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:13,160
then deal with it when I got the chance.

52
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:16,880
Careful, Xiaohe.

53
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:24,120
<i>I put it in the chicken coop.</i>

54
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:27,240
<i>I was afraid my uncle would find it.</i>

55
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:28,560
<i>So I thought</i>

56
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:31,400
<i>I should move it to a safer place.</i>

57
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:35,760
<i>But that drain inlet was too small.</i>

58
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:39,600
<i>No matter what, it wouldn't fit.</i>

59
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:42,680
<i>So I had to move it again.</i>

60
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:54,760
When I came back,
I found the head was gone.

61
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:56,600
I couldn't find it anywhere.

62
00:05:57,520 --> 00:05:58,920
So I took the bag

63
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,360
and buried it
in the woods behind the complex.

64
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:05,480
I was terrified for a long time,

65
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,920
having nightmares every day.

66
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:11,800
I went on like that for five years.

67
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:14,400
I thought it was over,

68
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,840
but then,

69
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:19,120
in the summer of 2002,

70
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:22,960
my uncle, Ge Jingsong,
pulled the head out.

71
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:25,200
Murder!

72
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:45,600
<i>Officer Ran went like a man possessed,</i>

73
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:49,720
<i>tearing through the whole complex,</i>
<i>searching everywhere.</i>

74
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:50,640
DANGER, ELECTRICITY

75
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,920
I was guilty and scared,

76
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:00,720
so I dug the bag back up

77
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:02,200
and moved it.

78
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:04,120
SO I MOVED THE BAG

79
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:07,360
But later, I almost got caught
by Officer Ran.

80
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:16,240
Open it.

81
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:18,960
At that time,

82
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:21,760
the underground garage
was under construction.

83
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:23,480
I took advantage of the moment

84
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:26,960
and stuffed the arm bones into the cement

85
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:28,680
and made a cement block.

86
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:31,840
I thought this time, no one would find it.

87
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:34,200
But I didn't expect,

88
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:36,480
after more than ten years,

89
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:40,160
I'd be the one to dig it up myself.

90
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:49,760
These bones have been
weighing on me ever since.

91
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:52,920
I hate Yuanlongli!

92
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:55,200
I hate it so much!

93
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:57,600
I wish it were torn down sooner!
Just tear it down!

94
00:07:57,680 --> 00:08:01,240
And these bones
and all the monsters all gone!

95
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:03,320
Gone for good!

96
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:06,560
Then no one would care
about this case anymore!

97
00:08:07,080 --> 00:08:08,120
Never again.

98
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:27,560
FAIR AND JUST, LOYAL AND TRUE

99
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:29,400
What Qian Dajun said is mostly reliable.

100
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:32,960
What he mentioned, the 1997 garage
and the rooftop incident,

101
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:35,080
I did go through
those things with Uncle Ran.

102
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:36,280
Preliminarily, it looks like Qian Dajun

103
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:38,880
has nothing to do with Xu Meng
and her father's deaths.

104
00:08:40,559 --> 00:08:41,679
Qian Dajun's arrest

105
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:44,680
means Yuanlongli
probably won't be demolished early.

106
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:47,040
<i>We still have time to keep investigating.</i>

107
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:51,320
Oh, and we should
circle back to Qian Dajun,

108
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:54,320
question him again about
everything related to the June 30th case.

109
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:57,440
<i>Maybe it'll lead to something bigger.</i>

110
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:58,360
Okay.

111
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:11,880
Uncle He.

112
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,800
Uncle He. Good afternoon.

113
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:17,200
I was just appointed by the company

114
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:22,120
as the Yuanlongli project's
head of redevelopment.

115
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:23,960
JIN MANLANG, RELOCATION MANAGER

116
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:31,000
The company also promised
that if the demolition wraps up quickly,

117
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:34,240
I'll be promoted to vice president.

118
00:09:34,760 --> 00:09:37,040
- So…
- So, what's that got to do with me?

119
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:39,120
Uncle He,

120
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:43,160
I'm not like Qian Dajun, I'm different.

121
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:46,200
I believe in sincerity

122
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:48,760
and peace above all.

123
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:57,040
Uncle He, this place,
I'm not renting this place anymore.

124
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:59,520
The rent will be returned double.

125
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:01,360
Please move out.

126
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,320
Double the rent.

127
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,960
Wait.

128
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:22,360
It's in black and white.
It's legal and valid.

129
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:25,680
I paid, so I have the right to stay
for three full months.

130
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:27,080
If you don't like it,

131
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:29,080
you can go to court and sue me.

132
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:31,120
How long it takes, I don't care.

133
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:33,880
Uncle He, let's talk this over.

134
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:36,000
I'll pay you triple rent.

135
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,000
Wang Laosan, come here.

136
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:43,040
Get out of here.

137
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:49,000
I've worked myself
to the bone all these years

138
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:52,200
and finally got my chance
to turn things around.

139
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:55,000
Now, anyone who gets in my way,

140
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:57,680
don't blame me, Jin Manlang,
for turning ruthless!

141
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:01,920
Who was it that said "peace above all"?

142
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:04,240
- Uncle He.
- See yourself out.

143
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:08,360
Well…

144
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:13,920
Wolf, don't get mad.

145
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:15,640
Peace above all.

146
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:17,640
Darn it!

147
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:22,400
Wolf. Wolf!

148
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:26,160
What's that?

149
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:28,280
- That bag looks heavy.
- Did you see that?

150
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:32,080
- That bag must be money.
- <i>Powering on.</i>

151
00:11:32,160 --> 00:11:34,920
<i>Good news! Good news!</i>

152
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:38,320
<i>The company has benefits for everyone!</i>

153
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:40,240
<i>100k yuan per household,</i>

154
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:41,800
<i>extra compensation.</i>

155
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:43,200
<i>Just sign the contract.</i>

156
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:44,520
- <i>Take the money now!</i>
- Let's go!

157
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:46,800
- Go take a look. Check it out.
- <i>Take the money now!</i>

158
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:48,440
- <i>Limited spots.</i>
- Me first.

159
00:11:48,520 --> 00:11:50,920
- <i>First come, first served!</i>
- Me first!

160
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:52,200
Is it real?

161
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:53,800
- They're really paying!
- Is it real?

162
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,480
Come on! Line up!

163
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:56,960
Line up, line up!

164
00:11:57,040 --> 00:11:58,400
<i>Benefits for everyone!</i>

165
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,040
Don't rush!

166
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:07,200
One at a time! Don't rush!

167
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:18,600
One at a time!

168
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:28,480
Meng, you've got to hold on,

169
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:30,280
stay and keep me company.

170
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:33,080
Don't let a little money blind you.

171
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:50,640
OFFICER HE, MENG'S BEEN DETAINED!

172
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:10,080
Let Mr. Meng enjoy this

173
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:13,040
Western symphony!

174
00:13:19,880 --> 00:13:21,120
So we're talking it out now?

175
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:23,040
No more fighting?

176
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:28,640
Why are you all staring at me?

177
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:30,920
Keep the music going.

178
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,080
Play something upbeat.

179
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:45,080
Can't you see the door's open?

180
00:13:45,160 --> 00:13:46,120
Hurry up.

181
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:49,280
Get Mr. Meng out here.

182
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:02,840
STAGED SCENE. DO NOT IMITATE

183
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:06,480
I'll send you all to hell!

184
00:14:06,560 --> 00:14:07,280
What are you doing?

185
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:08,600
You old fool, want to die?

186
00:14:08,680 --> 00:14:09,920
You brat!

187
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,520
I'll send you all to hell!

188
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,960
That's illegal! You hear me?

189
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:15,120
Call the police!

190
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:17,480
Call the police now!

191
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:19,040
I'll send you all to hell!

192
00:14:20,640 --> 00:14:21,760
<i>Come on!</i>

193
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:41,040
Wolfie, you just won't go away.

194
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:50,960
Uncle He.

195
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:53,880
Qiao, what are you doing here?

196
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:56,520
Come in, come in.

197
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:59,200
Well, what do you want to drink?
I'll get it.

198
00:14:59,280 --> 00:15:00,520
Uncle He, don't bother.

199
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:02,440
What's wrong?

200
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,200
I…

201
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:06,600
I didn't get our boss's approval,

202
00:15:07,680 --> 00:15:10,000
but I had finance sign off
on a 50k moving fee for you.

203
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:14,840
Qiao, what's going on?

204
00:15:16,360 --> 00:15:19,600
Didn't we agree
to fulfill Ran's wish together?

205
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:20,960
I know.

206
00:15:24,920 --> 00:15:27,600
I appreciate it, but I'm not moving.

207
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:31,120
No matter the offer,
no matter the money, I won't move.

208
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:32,280
That's final! You should go.

209
00:15:32,880 --> 00:15:35,440
Uncle He. Uncle He.

210
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:39,160
Our boss has reported you to the station.

211
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:43,760
You should be ready.

212
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:48,360
FORENSIC REPORT

213
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:56,840
Xia, Xia…

214
00:15:56,920 --> 00:15:59,200
Xiaohe, go to Captain Zhao's office.

215
00:15:59,280 --> 00:16:00,240
What's going on?

216
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:04,000
Captain Zhao, we're a private company.
It's not easy.

217
00:16:04,760 --> 00:16:07,960
This project can't be delayed anymore.

218
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:09,760
If He Yuanhang keeps this up,

219
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:12,160
it won't just hurt
our company's legal rights,

220
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:15,760
it'll also undermine
what the residents deserve.

221
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:20,080
Your criminal department
needs to stand up for people like us!

222
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:21,120
I understand.

223
00:16:21,640 --> 00:16:23,840
We will figure this out quickly

224
00:16:23,920 --> 00:16:25,200
and give you answers. Alright?

225
00:16:25,280 --> 00:16:26,680
Thank you, Captain Zhao.

226
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:29,560
Please hurry. This can't wait.

227
00:16:29,640 --> 00:16:30,960
Come on. I'll walk you out.

228
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:32,400
Okay, okay.

229
00:16:32,480 --> 00:16:33,600
- I'll head out then.
- Okay.

230
00:16:34,280 --> 00:16:36,200
Captain Zhao, stand up for us!

231
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:38,480
- Alright.
- Okay. Take care.

232
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:43,720
What's with He Yuanhang?

233
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:45,960
Has he lost it again?

234
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:55,600
Captain Zhao, Captain Qu,
since you're both here,

235
00:16:56,320 --> 00:16:57,240
I'd like to request

236
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:59,640
reopening the investigation
into the June 30th case.

237
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:03,360
June 30th?

238
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:04,760
That's ancient history.

239
00:17:04,839 --> 00:17:07,560
He Xiaohe, you're just as crazy
as your dad.

240
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:08,960
Isn't this mess enough?

241
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:11,720
Captain Zhao,

242
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:16,560
before Captain Ran passed,
he secretly reopened the June 30th case.

243
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:21,119
These days, my dad and I
have been retracing his investigation.

244
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:24,720
Now we have solid leads
proving Wu Shanlong was framed.

245
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:26,000
The real killer is someone else.

246
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:30,640
Any suspects?

247
00:17:32,440 --> 00:17:33,760
We are still checking.

248
00:17:36,480 --> 00:17:37,480
Not yet.

249
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:42,200
Captain Zhao,

250
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:44,760
this whole thing started because my dad

251
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:47,880
found an unsent message
on Uncle Ran's old phone.

252
00:17:58,280 --> 00:17:59,960
DRAFT, UNSENT MESSAGE
SAVED: 2003-01-31 13:09:37 TO: SIR

253
00:18:00,040 --> 00:18:01,600
RAN: SIR, THE JUNE 30TH CASE
WAS WRONG, ALL WRONG

254
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:04,360
This message was written
on the day he died.

255
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:11,080
Uncle Ran died with that regret.

256
00:18:21,280 --> 00:18:23,720
With the leads and evidence we have,
is it enough to reopen the case?

257
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:25,720
I trust my dad.

258
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:27,200
Just give him more time,

259
00:18:27,280 --> 00:18:29,400
he'll definitely find
key clues in Yuanlongli.

260
00:18:30,120 --> 00:18:30,960
We have to move fast.

261
